titleStmt.title: Droplaugarsona saga according to AM 132 fol : A digital edition

publicationStmt.date: Converted from database and adapted to Menota, 27 October 2017

msIdentifier.msName: Droplaugasona saga according to AM 132 fol (Möðruvallabók)

msContents.p: OEH: Description of the contents of the manuscript may be added here

origin.p: This manuscript was written in Iceland c. 1330-1370.

projectDesc.p: This encoding follows the standard set out in The Menota handbook (version 3.0), at http://www.menota.org/handbook.xml.
The encoded text has numbered pagebreaks, columnbreaks and linebreaks according to the manuscript.

normalization.p: This manuscript text has been encoded on three levels: facsimile, diplomatic and normalised.

correction.p: OEH: Comments on the correction may be added here.

interpretation.p: The text has been lemmatised and morphologically analysed according to the rules specified in ch. 11 of the Menota Handbook, v. 3.0

revisionDesc.change: 2021-07-11 Odd Einar Haugen University of Bergen: Revised and updated the header
2021-07-04 Nina Stensaker University of Bergen: Added some missing lb-elements.

2021-05-06 Odd Einar Haugen University of Bergen: Changed the following character entities according to the latest version of the Menota entity list: bisup > binodotsup, drotisup > drotinodotsup, hisup > hinodotsup, kisup > kinodotsup, thornisup > thorninodotsup, btit > ber, drottit > droter, htit > her, ktit > ker, thorntit > thorner, dvlig > drotvlig, dvligbar > drotvligmacr

(2) Encoded the "surplus" words, as found in the Fornrit edition by Jón Jóhannesson. These words are now morphAnalyzed.
2018-04-17 Andrea de Leeuw van Weenen: Distinguished between capitals/versals and enlarged minuscules
